article.headline: Long Beach State 77, UC Davis 48
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Shawn Hawkins tied a career high of 24 points in Long Beach State's 77-48 nonconference win over UC Davis Monday night. Hawkins scored eight straight Long Beach points in a six-minute span of the first half and had six points in a decisive 16-4 run in the second. He took down a game-high 11 rebounds for the 49ers (5-6). Jibril Hodges scored 12 points while Kevin Houston added 10 points. Davis (3-9) got 14 points from Vince Oliver and 10 points from Jesse Lopez Lowe. Long Beach shot 50 percent and Davis 33 percent.
